data.debugInfo:
The input image contained multiple Bill of Materials tables. As requested, only the data from the "DC-P1" table was extracted.

**Data Interpretation and Mapping:**
- The "DC-P1" table was identified as having two distinct sections: one for the main connector and a subsequent section for the individual wires connected to it.
- **Main Connector Row:**
    - "Qty / Length": Taken from the "QTY." column.
    - "Part #": Taken from the "PART #" column.
    - "MPN" and "Manufacturer": Parsed from the "DESCRIPTION" field, specifically "AMP P/N: 770520-1" was broken down into "MPN": "770520-1" and "Manufacturer": "AMP".
    - "Description / Wire Gauge": The remaining descriptive text from the "DESCRIPTION" column was used.
    - "Reference Notes": Left blank as no explicit notes were provided for the connector itself.
- **Wire Rows:**
    - Each row under the "WIRE" sub-section of the "DC-P1" table was treated as a separate item.
    - "Qty / Length": Left blank for all wire rows, as specific lengths or quantities (beyond implied '1 segment') were not provided in the source table.
    - "Part #": Populated directly from the "PIN PART #" column. Some entries in this column were visually blank in the source image; in these cases, the "Part #" field in the output JSON was left blank, as per instruction 3 (data missing or ambiguous). This column appears to be an identifier or internal part number for the specific wire segments.
    - "MPN" and "Manufacturer": Left blank for wire rows, as no manufacturer's part numbers or manufacturers were explicitly listed for these individual wire segments.
    - "Description / Wire Gauge": Combined from the "WIRE GAUGE" column (e.g., "16 GRY").
    - "Reference Notes": Populated from the "CONNECTED TO" column, indicating the destination or connection point of the wire.
